or an item that makes sense to use on this very character you played on the raid... no rolling on RBB for alts. this is really nothing special. i take it since i had random signups the people complaining about this are sorta raid newbies because this is commonly used rule on our server.<br><br>yes, that means casters could only roll for the bag (worth 5k) while melees/bards could roll for much more valuable scale or RBB<br><br>the monk bag trade in rule is also commonly used... if you're not a monk it doesn't matter if your bag has a weight of 0.4 or 1.0. if you are a monk it DOES matter. i have a lvl 53 monk alt and i'm exactly this 0.6 overweight. this didn't cause too much troubles though with the raid.<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>roll for one item only:</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>this is sorta special rule that i like to use. everyone can roll for one item only, no matter if you win or not, once you rolled you're out for other rolls. this makes the loot distribution more even.<br><br>in our case without this rule bards could've rolled for scale (4 rollers), rbb (13 rollers) AND the bag (about 25 rolles). casters could only roll for the bag, the lowest value item with a very low chance to get it.<br><br>being allowed to roll for one item only those who rolled for scale (4 rollers) and RBB (10 rollers) still had a much better chance to win a more valuable item than the caster who could roll for bag only (17 rollers). so if you complain about being allowed to roll for one item only the only reason that i can see is greed. <p>Baroness Camala Ironarm<BR>Epic Gemchopper Warlord<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zyen>zyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/24/02 6:56:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p